end on equipment and seek any advice other chanters can provide.  At this point I have no gear.  Thanks all. <p>Yours in Service,<BR>

Gotann Tantsor
Cleric of 55th Testament of Tunare <BR>

Warriors of Wrath</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulaelthedruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lael the Druid</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/01 1:13:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chanter Equipment Advice</span><hr size=1> My wife is a 55 chanter and she swears by CHA over INT.  With the clarity line of spells your mana will always come back fast (after 16) and your charisma will effect mez / charm abilities which is your trademark.  I am not that familiar with chanter gear forsay, just my advice on a general direction. <br>
<br>
Again just my 2cp. <p>Lael<br>
Wanderer of 54th Circle<br>
Proud Member and Officer of the Shattered Shield<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaelekin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daelekin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/30/01 2:56:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chanter Equipment Advice</span><hr size=1> I've heard from friends that getting your cha up to round the 180 range sould be plenty high enough, as for int bah thats easy to reach the 200 cap or very near that.  I'd think for chanter int/cha are important but also ac/hp would also mater quite a bit.  Chanters tent to get beat on quite a bit, guess them mobs dont' like being mezzed much, and as compared to other caster classes (with the exception of Clerics mostly) getting as much ac/hp as possible and keeping your int/cha up would prolly greatly aid you.  Also resists are a major plus for most caster classes I've noticed this is usually second choice after int in most cases for shear fact that good ac gear for pure casters if harder to come by.  However when AC would actually play a prevelent roll I have no idea for chanters since I primarily play a melee class, but I certainly can see when it would help.<br>
<br>
Daelekin<br>
Ranger of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulialoakshadowthebestdruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KulialOakshadowTheBestDruid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/10/01 9:57:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chanter Equipment Advice</span><hr size=1> my 13 chanter is erudin and this is what i have for the litle twink for now<br>
leggins=Drake-hide 5cha<br>
melee= rod of (something) glamour 13cha<br>
off hand= crude stien 15cha<br>
eariings= oppalline earrings or something like that 5cha each<br>
rings= golden star rubie 5cha each<br>
bracers= golden cats eye agate 7cha each<br>
waist=bcc 4int<br>
face= incandescent mask 7cha 5int<br>
gloves=incandescent gloves 3cha 3mana<br>
feet=jboots (sow like effect)<br>
arms=Gatorscale sleeves 4int<br>
shoulders=frozen mantle 10mana<br>
chect= robe of oracles 25mana 5int<br>
head=nightshade wrealth 5int<br>
<br>
As for the othere slots i am not sure what to get yet, these are not all the stats to the items just the stats for cha/int<br>
Kulial Oakshadow<br>
52nd Wanderer<br>
Circle of Justice<br>
<br>
Darkahn<br>
13th Enchanter<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaryinnmb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maryinn MB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/11/01 11:17:07 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.merryband.com/images/maryinn/maryinn_2.jpg width=165 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chanter Equipment Advice</span><hr size=1> In the long term you'll want to look at gathering hp items.  Most high level enchanters have more cha and int than they need, what they need is to take more hits and hps will allow that more than anything else.  Charisma isn't as important as some people think.  People have studied the value of charisma and the consensus is that it plays only a small role in your mez/charm rates.  I wouldn't worry about getting cha beyond 150ish.  Mine stays at 130-140 unbuffed and there isn't a significant difference between that and when I'm buffed to 200ish.<br>
<br>
At level 60 I have nearly 1600 hps unbuffed.  I'm sure the lead enchanters/pure casters in some of the larger guilds are closing in on 2000 hps unbuffed. <p>-<a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=998">Maryinn</a> 
<<a href="http://www.merryband.com">Merry Band</a>> (<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis">Brell Serilis</a>)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanyesillow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanyesillow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/13/01 8:33:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chanter Equipment Advice</span><hr size=1> I would advise going for int/cha gear at lower lev but as previous posts stated ya can get that up fairly easy...higher lev like me at lev 57 is definately a pursuit for resist gear and hp/ac ....most of the time I cant solo too much this high anyway and so i group and usually end up with 2400+ hps from clerics or buffers in group...so definately get resists up and worry about other attributes besides cha/int...mana is important too...also concentrate getting your research out of way early when low lev so ya get important needed spells...<br>
<br>
Sanye Sillow<br>
57 Chantress of Skyre Draneth <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=598.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=578.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=577.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=577.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=577.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm67">Today's News<option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisroleplaying">The Tavern (Roleplaying)<option value="brellserilisfrm66">Rants Link<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisfrm64">Archived Threads<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: Ra